obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39577)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) Act, 1971.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39577&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39578)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39578&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) “Administrator” means the administrator of a Union territory appointed by the President under`
  line `article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) “appointed day” means the day^1 which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(c) “article” means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(d) “common High Court” means the Gauhati High Court (the High Court of Assam, Nagaland,`
  line `Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura) referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 28:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided that on and from the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation)`
  line `and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, the provisions of this clause shall have effect as if`
  line `for the brackets and words “(Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura)”, the brackets and`
  line `words “(Assam, Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram and Nagaland)” had been substituted;]`
  line
  line `(e) “Election Commission” means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;`
  line
  line `(f) “existing State of Assam” means the State of Assam as existing immediately before the`
  line `appointed day;`
  line
  line `(g) “law” includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme, notification`
  line `or other instrument having, immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the whole or any`
  line `part of the existing State of Assam or the autonomous State of Meghalaya or the Union territory of`
  line `Manipur or the Union territory of Tripura, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(h) “sitting member”, in relation to either House of Parliament or the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `existing State of Assam, means a person who, immediately before the appointed day, is a member of`
  line `that House or that Assembly;`
  line
  line `(i) “successor State”, in relation to the existing State of Assam, means the State of Assam or`
  line `Meghalaya, and includes also the Union in relation to the Union territory of Mizoram;`
  line
  line `(j) “treasury” includes a sub-treasury.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21st January, 1972, vide notification No. G.S.R. 18(E), dated 6th January, 1972, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `s. 3(i).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39579)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the State of Manipur.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39579&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day there shall be`
  line `established a new State, to be known as the State of Manipur, comprising the territories which`
  line `immediately before that day were comprised in the Union territory of Manipur.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39580)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of the State of Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39580&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day there shall be established`
  line `a new State, to be known as the State of Tripura, comprising the territories which immediately before that`
  line `day were comprised in the Union territory of Tripura.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39581)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Formation of the State of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39581&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day there shall be formed a`
  line `new State, to be known as the State of Meghalaya, comprising—`
  line
  line `(a) the territories which immediately before that day were comprised in the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya formed under section 3 of the Assam Reorganisation (Meghalaya) Act, 1969 (55 of 1969);`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) so much of the territories comprised within the cantonment and municipality of Shillong as did`
  line `not form part of that autonomous State,`
  line
  line `and thereupon the said territotries shall cease to form part of the existing State of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39582)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Formation of the Union territory of Mizoram.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39582&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day there shall be`
  line `formed a new Union territory, to be known as the Union territory of Mizoram, comprising the territories`
  line `which immediately before that day were comprised in the Mizo District in the existing State of Assam and`
  line `thereupon the said territories shall cease to form part of the existing State of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39583)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Formation of the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39583&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day there`
  line `shall be formed a new Union territory, to be known as the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh,`
  line `comprising the territories which immediately before that day were comprised in the tribal areas specified`
  line `in Part B of the table appended to paragraph 20 of the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution (but excluding`
  line `the areas covered by notification No. TAD/R/35/50/109, dated the 23rd February, 1951 issued by the`
  line `Governor of Assam under the proviso to sub-paragraph (3) of the said paragraph 20) and known as the`
  line `North-East Frontier Agency and thereupon the said territories shall cease to form part of the existing State`
  line `of Assam.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39584)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Territories of the State of the Assam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39584&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day the State of Assam shall`
  line `comprise the territories of the existing State of Assam other than those specified in sections 5, 6 and 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39585)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Amendment of first Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39585&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution,—`
  line
  line `(a) under the heading "I. THE STATES",—`
  line
  line `(i) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Assam, the following shall be`
  line `added at the end, namely:—`
  line
  line `"and the territories specified in sections 5, 6 and 7 of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) Act, 1971";`
  line
  line `(ii) after entry 18 the following entries shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"19. Manipur The territory which immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Constitution was being administered as if it were a Chief Commissioner's`
  line `Province under the name of Manipur.`
  line
  line `20. Tripura The territory which immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Constitution was being administered as if it were a Chief Commissioner's`
  line `Province under the name of Tripura.`
  line
  line `21. Meghalaya The territories specified in section 5 of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) Act, 1971.";`
  line
  line `(b) under the heading "II. THE UNION TERRITORIES".—`
  line
  line `(i) entries 2 and 3 shall be omitted and entries 4 to 9 shall be re-numbered as entries 2 to 7`
  line respectively;
  line
  line `(ii) after entry 7 as so re-numbered, the following entries shall be inserted, namely:`
  line
  line `"8. Mizoram The territories specified in section 6 of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) Act, 1971.`
  line
  line `9. Arunachal The territories specified in section 7 of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) Act, 1971.".`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39586)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Amendment of Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39586&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the`
  line `Fourth Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table,—`
  line
  line `(a) for entries 19 to 22, the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"19. Manipur .. 1`
  line
  line `20. Tripura .. 1`
  line
  line `21. Meghalaya .. 1`
  line
  line `22. Delhi .. 3`
  line
  line `23. Pondicherry .. 1`
  line
  line `24. Mizoram .. 1`
  line
  line `25. Arunachal Pradesh .. 1";`
  line
  line `(b) for the figures "228", the figures "231" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39587)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Allocation of sitting members representing the existing Union territories of Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39587&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day the sitting members of the Council of States representing the`
  line `existing Union territories of Manipur and Tripura shall be deemed to have been duly elected under`
  line `clause (4) of article 80 to fill the seat allotted to each of the States of Manipur and Tripura respectively in`
  line `that Council and the term of office of such sitting members shall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39677)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Election to fill the seats allotted to the State of Meghalaya and the Union territories of Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39677&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the appointed day steps shall be taken to`
  line `fill the seats in the Council of States allotted to the State of Meghalaya and the Union territories of`
  line `Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39589)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Amendment of section 27A of Act 43 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39589&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in section 27A`
  line `of the Representation of the People Act, 1950,—`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words "For the purpose of filling any seat", the words, brackets and`
  line `figure "Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), for the purpose of filling any seat" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), for the words "The electoral college for each of the Union territories of`
  line `Manipur, Tripura and Pondicherry", the words "The electoral college for the Union territory of`
  line `Pondicherry" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) after sub-section (4), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(5) The seat allotted in the Council of State to each of the Union territories of Mizoram and`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh shall be filled by a person nominated by the President in this behalf."`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39590)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Allocation of seats in the existing House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39590&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day and`
  line `until the dissolution of the existing House of the People, the allocation of seats to the States of Assam,`
  line `Manipur, Tripura and Meghalaya and the Union territories of Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh in the`
  line `House of the People and the number of seats, if any, to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and for the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes of each State and Union territory shall be as specified in the Table below and the First`
  line `Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), shall be deemed to have been`
  line `amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `THE TABLE`
  line
  line `Name of the State/Union`
  line territory
  line `Number of seats in the existing House of the`
  line People
  line `Total Reserved for`
  line `the Scheduled`
  line Castes
  line `Reserved for`
  line `the Scheduled`
  line Tribes
  line
  line `1 2 3 4`
  line
  line `I. STATES:`
  line
  line `1. Assam . . . 14 1 2`
  line
  line `2. Manipur . . . 2 .. 1`
  line
  line `3. Tripura . . . 2 .. 2`
  line
  line `4. Meghalaya . . . 2 .. 2`
  line
  line `II. UNION TERRITORIES:`
  line
  line `1. Mizoram . . . 1 .. 1`
  line
  line `2. Arunachal`
  line Pradesh
  line `. . . 1 .. 1`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day and until the dissolution of the existing House of the People, Part A`
  line `of Schedule II to the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1966 shall stand`
  line `amended as directed in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39676)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Parliamentary constituencies of the States of Manipur and Tripura and provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39676&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day and until the dissolution of the existing House of`
  line `the People,—`
  line
  line `(a) the two parliamentary constituencies of the existing Union territory of Manipur shall be`
  line `deemed to be the two parliamentary constituencies of the State of Manipur; and`
  line
  line `(b) the two parliamentary constituencies of the existing Union territory of Tripura shall be deemed`
  line `to be the two parliamentary constituencies of the State of Tripura,`
  line
  line `and the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1966 shall be construed`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) Every sitting member of the House of the People representing a parliamentary constituency which`
  line `on the appointed day, by virtue of the provisions of sub-section (1), becomes a parliamentary constituency of the State of Manipur or Tripura, as the case may be, shall, as from that day, be deemed to have been`
  line `elected under sub-clause (a) of clause (1) of article 81 to the House of the People from that constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39678)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Provision as to sitting members representing Cachar and Dhubri parliamentary constituencies in the House of the People and the election of representative from Diphu parliamentary constituency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39678&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sitting member of the House of the People representing the Cachar`
  line `parliamentary constituency which on the appointed day, by virtue of the provisions of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14, stands altered shall, as from that day, be deemed to have been elected under sub-clause (a) of`
  line `clause (1) of article 81 to the House of the People from that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting member of the House of the People representing the Dhubri parliamentary constituency`
  line `which on the appointed day, by virtue of the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 14, stands altered`
  line `shall, as from that day, be deemed to have been elected under sub-clause (a) of clause (1) of article 81 to`
  line `the House of the People from that constituency as so altered.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as may be after the appointed day election shall be held to the House of the People to elect`
  line `a representative from the Diphu parliamentary constituency as if the seat of the member elected to the`
  line `House of the People from that constituency has become vacant and the provisions of section 149 of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such`
  line election.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39679)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Parliamentary constituencies of the State of Meghalaya and provision as to sitting member representing the Autonomous Districts parliamentary constituency in the House of the People and the election of representative from Tura parliamentary constituency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39679&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be two`
  line `parliamentary constituencies in the State of Meghalaya to be called the Shillong parliamentary`
  line `constituency and the Tura parliamentary constituency.`
  line
  line `(2) The area falling within the Garo Hills district as it exists immediately before the appointed day`
  line `shall form the Tura parliamentary constituency and the remaining area in the State of Meghalaya shall`
  line `form the Shillong parliamentary constituency and the said two parliamentary constituencies shall be`
  line `deemed to have been delimited accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) The sitting member of the House of the People representing immediately before the appointed day`
  line `the Autonomous Districts parliamentary constituency shall, as from that day, be deemed to have been`
  line `elected under sub-clause (a) of clause (1) of article 81 to the House of the People from the Shillong`
  line `parliamentary constituency.`
  line
  line `(4) As soon as may be after the appointed day election shall be held to the House of the People to elect`
  line `a representative from the Tura parliamentary constituency as if the seat of the member elected to the`
  line `House of the People from that constituency has become vacant and the provisions of section 149 of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such`
  line election.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39594)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Parliamentary constituency of the Union territory of Mizoram.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39594&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The whole of the Union`
  line `territory of Mizoram shall form one parliamentary constituency to be called the Mizoram parliamentary`
  line `constituency and as soon as may be after the appointed day election shall be held to the House of the`
  line `People to elect a representative from that constituency, as if the seat of the member elected to the House of`
  line `the People from that constituency has become vacant and the provisions of section 149 of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such`
  line election.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39595)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Provision as to the member to represent Arunachal Pradesh in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39595&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line The
  line `sitting member nominated to fill the seat allotted in the House of the People to the Tribal Areas of Assam`
  line `specified in Part B of the Table appended to paragraph 20 of the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution,`
  line `known as the North-East Frontier Agency, shall, on and from the appointed day, be deemed to have been`
  line `nominated to fill the seat allotted to the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh in the House of the People.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39596)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Allocation of seats in the Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39596&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the total`
  line `number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam, to be filled by persons chosen by direct`
  line `election from territorial constituencies, shall be reduced from one hundred and twenty-six to one hundred`
  line `and fourteen; and every sitting member of that Legislative Assembly representing a constituency which`
  line `ceases to be a constituency in the State of Assam by virtue of the provisions of sub-section (5) shall, as`
  line `from the appointed day, cease to be a member of that Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of the State of Manipur, to be constituted at`
  line `any time after the appointed day, to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from territorial`
  line `constituencies shall be sixty, out of which one seat shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and nineteen`
  line `seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(3) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of the State of Tripura, to be constituted at`
  line `any time after the appointed day, to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from territorial`
  line `constituencies shall be sixty, out of which six seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and nineteen`
  line `seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(4) The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya, to be constituted`
  line `at any time after the appointed day, to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from territorial`
  line `constituencies shall be sixty, out of which fifty seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(5) On and from the appointed day, Part B of Schedule II to the Delimitation of Parliamentary and`
  line `Assembly Constituencies Order, 1966 shall stand amended as directed in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39597)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Amendment of Second Schedule to Act 43 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39597&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1950,—`
  line
  line `(i) under the heading "I. STATES:",—`
  line
  line `(a) in item 2 relating to Assam, for the figures 126, the figures "114" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) after item 17 and the entries relating thereto, the following shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"18. Manipur .. 60 1 19`
  line
  line `19. Tripura .. 60 6 19`
  line
  line `20. Meghalaya .. 60 .. 50";`
  line
  line `(ii) under the heading "II. UNION TERRITORIES:" items 3 and 5 and the entries relating thereto`
  line `shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `(2) The amendment made by clause (i)(a) of sub-section (1) shall have effect on and after the`
  line `appointed day in relation to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam and the amendments made by`
  line `clause (i)(b) and clause (ii) of sub-section (1) shall have effect in relation to the Legislative Assemblies of`
  line `the States of Manipur, Tripura and Meghalaya to be constituted at any time after the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39598)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39598&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election Commission shall, in the manner herein`
  line `provided, distribute, whether before or after the appointed day, the seats assigned to the Legislative`
  line `Assemblies of the States of Manipur, Tripura and Meghalaya under section 20 to single member territorial`
  line `constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the latest census figures having regard to the provisions of`
  line `the Constitution and to the following provisions:—`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, so far as practicable, be geographically compact areas and in`
  line `delimiting them, regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units,`
  line `facilities of communication and public convenience;`
  line
  line `(b) every assembly constituency shall be so delimited as to fall only within one parliamentary`
  line constituency;
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes shall be distributed in`
  line `different parts of the States and located, as far as practicable, in those areas where the proportion of`
  line `their population to the total population is comparatively large; and`
  line
  line `(d) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Tribes shall, as far as practicable,`
  line `be located in those areas where the proportion of their population to the total population is the largest.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section "latest census figures" means the census figures with respect to the State`
  line `concerned ascertainable from the latest census of which the finally published figures are available.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of assisting in the performance of its functions under sub-section (1), the Election`
  line `Commission shall associate with itself as associate members,—`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the State of Manipur, all the sitting members of the House of the People`
  line `representing the Union territory of Manipur or, as the case may be, the State of Manipur under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15, and such six persons who were members of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the Union territory of Manipur immediately before its dissolution by order of the President published`
  line `in the Gazette of India, dated 16th October, 1969 with notification No. S. O. 4223, dated 16th October,`
  line `1969 of the Government of India in the Ministry of Home Affairs, as the President may, by order,`
  line nominate;
  line
  line `(b) in respect of the State of Tripura, all the sitting members of the House of the People`
  line `representing the Union territory of Tripura or, as the case may be, the State of Tripura under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15, and such six persons, being members of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the Union territory of Tripura as it functioned immediately before the 1st November, 1971, as the`
  line `President may, by order, nominate;`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of the State of Meghalaya, the member of the House of the People representing the`
  line `Autonomous Districts parliamentary constituency or, as the case may be, the Meghalaya parliamentary`
  line `constituency under section 17, and such of the six members of the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `autonomous State of Meghalaya constituted under section 62 of the Assam Reorganisation`
  line `(Meghalaya) Act, 1969 ( 55 of 1969) or, as the case may be, of the Provisional Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the State of Meghalaya referred to in section 27, as the President may, by order, nominate:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate members shall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) If owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled, if`
  line `practicable, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) A member of any Legislative Assembly nominated under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (2)`
  line `shall continue to be an associate member notwithstanding that he ceases to be a member of such`
  line `Legislative Assembly, otherwise than consequent on the incurring of any disqualification.`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies, together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof, in the Official Gazette and`
  line `in such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections`
  line `and suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will`
  line `be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(c) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause such`
  line `order or orders to be published in the Official Gazette; and upon such publication, the order or orders`
  line `shall have the full force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(6) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order shall be laid before the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the concerned State.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39599)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Election Commission to maintain delimitation orders up-to-date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39599&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election`
  line `Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,—`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any order made under section 22 or any error arising therein`
  line `from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order or orders`
  line `are or is altered, make such amendment as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such`
  line `order up-to-date.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued, before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the concerned State.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39600)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Validation of acts done previous to the commencement of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39600&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All things done, and all`
  line `steps taken, before the commencement of this Act with a view to delimiting the territorial constituencies of`
  line `the States of Manipur, Tripura and Meghalaya for the purpose of elections to the Legislative Assemblies`
  line `of those States shall, in so far as they are in conformity with the provisions of sections 22 and 23, be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under those sections as if those sections were in force at the time such`
  line `things were done or such steps were taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39601)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Amendment of Scheduled Castes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39601&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950 shall stand amended as directed in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution (Scheduled Castes) (Union Territories) Order,`
  line `1951 shall stand amended as directed in the Third Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39602)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Amendment of Scheduled Tribes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39602&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950 shall stand amended as directed in the Fourth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution (Scheduled Tribes) (Union Territories) Order,`
  line `1951 shall stand amended as directed in the Fifth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39685)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provision as to Provisional Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya and as to Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the Legislative Assemblies of the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39685&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day and until the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `State of Meghalaya has been duly constituted and summoned to meet for the first session under the`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, the Provisional Legislative Assembly of the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya, excluding the members nominated thereto, constituted under section 62 of the Assam`
  line `Reorganisation (Meghalaya) Act, 1969 (55 of 1969) and functioning immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, shall be the Provisional Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya and that Assembly shall`
  line `exercise all the powers and perform all the duties conferred by the provisions of the Constitution on the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of that State:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of this sub-section, the member representing the autonomous District of`
  line `United Khasi-Jaintia Hills in the said Provisional Legislative Assembly of the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya shall be deemed also to represent the territories specified in clause (b) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the members of the Provisional Legislative Assembly of the State of`
  line `Meghalaya shall, unless the said Legislative Assembly is sooner dissolved, expire immediately before the`
  line `first meeting of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons who, immediately before the appointed day, are the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker`
  line `of the Provisional Legislative Assembly of the autonomous State of Meghalaya shall be the Speaker and`
  line `the Deputy Speaker respectively of the Provisional Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(4) The Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the Provisional Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `autonomous State of Meghalaya, as in force immediately before the appointed day, shall, until rules are`
  line `made under clause (1) of article 208, be the Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the`
  line `Provisional Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya and of the Legislative Assembly of the State`
  line `of Meghalaya duly constituted under the provisions of the Constitution, subject to such adaptations as may`
  line `be made therein by the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly, concerned.`
  line
  line `(5) The Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory of Manipur, as in force immediately before its dissolution by order of the President published in`
  line `the Gazette of India, dated the 16th October, 1969 with notification No. S.O. 4223, dated the 16th October,`
  line `1969 of the Government of India in the Ministry of Home Affairs, shall, until rules are made under clause`
  line `(1) of article 208, be the Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the Legislative Assembly of the`
  line `State of Manipur, subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Governor`
  line `of that State.`
  line
  line `(6) The Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the Legislative Assembly of the Union`
  line `territory of Tripura as in force immediately before the 1st November, 1971, shall, until rules are made`
  line `under clause (1) of article 208, be the Rules of Procedure and Conduct of Business of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the State of Tripura, subject to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by`
  line `the Governor of that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39604)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Common High Court for Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 3 (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39604&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and`
  line `from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the High Court of Assam and Nagaland shall cease to function and is hereby abolished;`
  line
  line `(b) there shall be a common High Court for the States of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur`
  line `and Tripura to be called the Gauhati High Court (the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya,`
  line `Manipur and Tripura);`
  line
  line `(c) the Judges of the High Court of Assam and Nagaland holding office immediately before that`
  line `day shall, unless they have elected otherwise, become on that day the Judges of the common`
  line `High Court:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that on and from the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation)`
  line `and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, the common High Court shall be the High`
  line `Court for the States of Assam, Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram and Nagaland and shall cease to have`
  line `its jurisdiction, powers and authority for the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.]`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall prejudice or affect the continued operation of any`
  line `notice served, injunction issued, direction given or proceedings taken before the appointed day by the`
  line `High Court of Assam and Nagaland under the powers then conferred upon that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (39605)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 29
  title `Establishment of separate High Courts for the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39605&sectionno=28A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[28A. Establishment of separate High Courts for the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and`
  line `Tripura.—(1) On and from the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other`
  line `Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, there shall be a High Court—`
  line
  line `(a) for the State of Meghalaya to be called the High Court of Meghalaya;`
  line
  line `(b) for the State of Manipur to be called the High Court of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(c) for the State of Tripura to be called the High Court of Tripura.`
  line
  line `(2) The principal seat of the High Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court`
  line `of Tripura shall respectively be at such place as the President may, by notified order, appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Judges and division courts of the`
  line `High Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura may sit at such other`
  line `place or places in the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura respectively, other than their principal`
  line `seat as the Chief Justice of the respective High Court may, with the approval of the Governor of the State`
  line `concerned, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b:
  sectionId (39606)
  sectionNo 28B
  orderNo 30
  title `Judges of High Courts of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39606&sectionno=28B&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such of the Judges of the`
  line `common High Court holding office immediately before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas`
  line `(Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 as may be determined by the President`
  line `after ascertaining their option shall, on such commencement, cease to be the Judges of the common High`
  line `Court and become a Judge of the High Court of Meghalaya or the High Court of Manipur or the High`
  line `Court of Tripura, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who by virtue of sub-section (1) become a Judge of the High Court of Meghalaya or`
  line `the High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura shall, except in the case where any such person is`
  line `appointed to be the Chief Justice of any of those High Courts, rank in the respective High Court according`
  line `to the priority of their respective appointments as Judges of the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_c:
  sectionId (39607)
  sectionNo 28C
  orderNo 31
  title `Jurisdiction of High Courts of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39607&sectionno=28C&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_c_content:
  string
  line `The High Court of`
  line `Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura shall have, in respect of any part of`
  line `the territories included in the State of Meghalaya, the State of Manipur and the State of Tripura`
  line `respectively, all such jurisdiction, powers and authority as, under the law in force immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2012, are exercisable in respect of that part of the said territories by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_d:
  sectionId (39608)
  sectionNo 28D
  orderNo 32
  title `Custody of seal of High courts of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39608&sectionno=28D&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_d_content:
  string
  line `The law in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 with respect to the custody of the seal of the common High Court shall,`
  line `with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of`
  line `Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_e:
  sectionId (39609)
  sectionNo 28E
  orderNo 33
  title `Practice and procedure in the High Courts of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39609&sectionno=28E&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_e_content:
  string
  line `The law`
  line `in force immediately before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other`
  line `Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 with respect to practice and procedure in the common High Court`
  line `shall, with necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of`
  line `Manipur and the High Court of Tripura, and accordingly, the High Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of`
  line `Manipur and the High Court of Tripura shall, respectively, have all such powers to make rules and orders`
  line `with respect to practice and procedure as are immediately before the commencement of the North-Eastern`
  line `Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 exercisable by the common`
  line `High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that any rules or orders which are in force immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 with respect to`
  line `the practice and procedure in the common High Court shall, until varied or revoked by rules or orders`
  line `made by the High Court of Meghalaya or the High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura, as the`
  line `case may be, apply with the necessary modifications in relation to the practice and procedure in the High`
  line `Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura respectively, as if such`
  line `rules or orders were made by the respective High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_e_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_f:
  sectionId (39610)
  sectionNo 28F
  orderNo 34
  title `Forms of writs and other processes.`
