obj_root_law_sections_28_f_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the commencement`
  line `of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 with`
  line `respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the common High Court shall,`
  line `with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued`
  line `or awarded by the High Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_f_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_g:
  sectionId (39611)
  sectionNo 28G
  orderNo 35
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39611&sectionno=28G&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_g_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 relating to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, Single Judges and division courts of the common High Court and with`
  line `respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary modifications,`
  line `apply in relation to the High Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of`
  line Tripura.
obj_root_law_sections_28_g_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_h:
  sectionId (39612)
  sectionNo 28H
  orderNo 36
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39612&sectionno=28H&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_h_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2012 relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the common High Court and the Judges and division courts thereof shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Courts of Meghalaya,`
  line `Manipur and Tripura.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_h_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_i:
  sectionId (39680)
  sectionNo 28-I
  orderNo 37
  title `Transfer of proceedings from common High Court to the High Courts of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39680&sectionno=28-I&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_i_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided, the common High Court shall, as from the`
  line `commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2012, have no jurisdiction in respect of the States of Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the common High Court immediately before the commencement of`
  line `the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 as are`
  line `certified, whether before or after that day, by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the`
  line `place of accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances to be proceedings which ought to be heard`
  line `and decided by the High Court of Meghalaya or the High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura,`
  line `as the case may be, shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Meghalaya or the High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1)@ i@ and (2) or in section 28A, but save as`
  line `hereinafter provided, the common High Court shall have, and the High Court of Meghalaya, the High`
  line `Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura shall not have, jurisdication to entertain, hear or dispose`
  line `of appeals, applications for leave to the Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings`
  line `where any such proceedings seek any relief in respect of any order passed by the common High Court`
  line `before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2012:`
  line
  line `Provided that if after any such proceedings have been entertained by the common High Court, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Meghalaya or the High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura, he shall order that they shall be so`
  line `transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the common High Court--`
  line
  line `(a) before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Meghalaya, or the`
  line `High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura by virtue of sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceeding with respect to which the common High Court retains jurisdiction by virtue`
  line `of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect, not only as an order of the common High Court but also as an order`
  line `made by the High Court of Meghalaya, or the High Court of Manipur or the High Court of Tripura, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_i_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_j:
  sectionId (39613)
  sectionNo 28J
  orderNo 38
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39613&sectionno=28J&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_j_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 28H,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a Court until that Court has disposed of all`
  line `issues between the parties, including any issue with respect to the taxation of the costs of the`
  line `proceedings and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court,`
  line `applications for review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs; and`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `Court thereof, and references to an order made by a Court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that Court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_j_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28_k:
  sectionId (39614)
  sectionNo 28K
  orderNo 39
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39614&sectionno=28K&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_28_k_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in sections 28A to 28J (both inclusive) shall affect the application to the High`
  line `Court of Meghalaya, the High Court of Manipur and the High Court of Tripura of any provisions of the`
  line `Constitution, and the provisions of these sections shall have effect subject to any provision that may be`
  line `made on or after the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 with respect to the respective High Court by any Legislature or other`
  line `authority having power to make such provisions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_k_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39615)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 40
  title `Jurisdiction of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39615&sectionno=29&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the common`
  line `High Court shall have, in respect of the territories comprised in the States of Assam, Manipur,`
  line `Meghalaya, Nagaland and Tripura, all such jurisdiction, powers and authority as under the law in force`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, are exercisable in respect of those territories by the High Court of`
  line `Assam and Nagaland or the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Manipur, or the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner for Tripura, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39616)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 41
  title `Abolition of certain Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39616&sectionno=30&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Courts of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioners for Manipur and Tripura shall cease to function and are hereby abolished.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall prejudice or affect the continued operation of any notice served,`
  line `injunction issued, direction given or proceedings taken before the appointed day by any of the Courts`
  line `abolished by that sub-section, under the powers then conferred upon that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39617)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 42
  title `Principal seat and other places of sitting of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 5, for "Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Nagaland or Tripura" (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39617&sectionno=31&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The principal seat of`
  line `the common High Court shall be at the same place at which the principal seat of the High Court of Assam`
  line `and Nagaland is located immediately before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The President may by notified order provide for the establishment of a permanent bench or`
  line `benches of the common High Court at one or more places within the territories to which the jurisdiction of`
  line `the High Court extends, other than the principal seat of the High Court, and for any matters connected`
  line `therewith:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any order under this sub-section, the President shall consult the Chief`
  line `Justice of the common High Court and the Governor of the State in which the bench or benches is or are`
  line `proposed to be established.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Judges and division`
  line `courts of the common High Court may also sit at such other place or places in the State of ^1`
  line [Assam,
  line `Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram or Nagaland] as the Chief Justice may, with the approval of the Governor of`
  line `the State concerned, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39681)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 43
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of the common High Court to the Union territories of Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39681&sectionno=32&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, the jurisdiction of the common High Court shall`
  line `extend to the Union territories of Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that on and from the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and`
  line `Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, the provisions of this section shall cease to have effect.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39619)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 44
  title `Allocation of expenditure of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "Manipur, Meghalaya, Nagaland and Tripura" (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39619&sectionno=33&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The expenditure in respect of salaries`
  line `and allowances of the Judges of the common High Court shall be allocated amongst the States of`
  line ^1
  line `[Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram and Nagaland] and the Union in such proportion as the President may, by`
  line `order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39620)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 45
  title `Special provisions relating to advocates and Bar Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39620&sectionno=34&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rule made or`
  line `direction given by the common High Court in this behalf, any person, who immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Assam and Nagaland or in the Court`
  line `of the Judicial Commissioner for Manipur or in the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Tripura, shall`
  line `be entitled to practise as an advocate in the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The right of audience in the common High Court shall be regulated in accordance with the like`
  line `principles as, immediately before the appointed day, are in force with respect to the right of audience in`
  line `the High Court of Assam and Nagaland:`
  line
  line `Provided that as among the Advocates-General of the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya,`
  line `Nagaland and Tripura, the right of audience shall be determined with reference to their dates of enrolment`
  line `as advocates.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the appointed day, in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) (hereafter in this Part`
  line `referred to as the Advocates Act), in section 3,—`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(i) for clause (b), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(b) for the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Nagaland and Tripura and the Union`
  line `territories of Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh, to be known as the Bar Council of Assam,`
  line `Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.";`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (e), for the words "Union territories of Tripura and the Andaman and Nicobar`
  line `Islands", the words "Union territory of the Andaman and Nicobar Islands" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), in clause (b), for the words "Bar Council of Assam", the words "Bar`
  line `Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of section 17 of the Advocates Act shall have effect in respect of the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura subject to the modifications that,—`
  line
  line `(a) for clause (a) of sub-section (1) of the said section 17, the following clause shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"(a) all persons who were entered as advocates,—`
  line
  line `(i) on the roll of the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland immediately before the day`
  line `appointed under clause (b) of section 2 of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) Act,`
  line 1971;
  line
  line `(ii) on the roll of the Bar Council of West Bengal immediately before that day and who,`
  line `within three months from that day, express in such manner as the Bar Council of India may,`
  line `by rules, prescribe their intention in writing to practise within the jurisdiction of the Bar`
  line `Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura;";`
  line
  line `(b) in clause (a) of sub-section (3) of the said section 17, for the words and figures "with his date`
  line `of enrolment under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926," (38 of 1926) the words "with his seniority on`
  line `the roll of the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland or, as the case may be, the Bar Council of West`
  line `Bengal" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Advocates Act, as amended or modified by`
  line `sub-sections (3) and (4),—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the first Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura`
  line `under that Act, the fifteen members required to be elected under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 3 of that Act, shall be nominated by the Chief Justice of the common High Court from`
  line `amongst the advocates who are entitled as of right of practise in that High Court and are ordinarily`
  line `practising within the territories comprised in the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya, Nagaland and`
  line `Tripura and the Union territories of Mizoram and Arunachal Pradesh and the term of office of the`
  line `members so nominated shall be one year from the date of the first meeting of the Council or until`
  line `their successors are duly elected in accordance with the provisions of the said Act, whichever is`
  line earlier;
  line
  line `(b) the names of persons entered on the roll of the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya,`
  line `Manipur and Tripura from the roll of the Bar Council of West Bengal in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 17 of the Advocates Act, as modified by`
  line `sub-section (4), shall, as from the date or dates on which the names are so entered, stand removed`
  line `from the roll of the Bar Council of West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(c) any proceedings which were pending or which may be instituted against any person before or`
  line `by the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland or by the Bar Council of West Bengal immediately before`
  line `his name is entered in the roll of the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura in accordance with the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 17 of the`
  line `Advocates Act, as modified by sub-section (4), may, after such entry, be continued or instituted`
  line `before or by the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura;`
  line
  line `(d) every person who, immediately before his name stands removed from the roll of the`
  line `Bar Council of West Bengal in accordance with the provisions of clause (b), is a member of the`
  line `Bar Council of West Bengal, shall cease to be a member of that Council as from the date on which his`
  line `name stands so removed from the roll of that Bar Council;`
  line
  line `(e) the rules made or deemed to have been made by the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland and`
  line `in force immediately before the date on which the first Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya,`
  line `Manipur and Tripura is duly constituted in accordance with the provisions of clause (a), shall, subject`
  line `to such modifications and adaptations as may be made therein by the Chairman of the Bar Council of`
  line `Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura, be deemed to be rules made by that Bar Council`
  line `and shall have effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(6)(a) As from the appointed day, the assets and liabilities of the Bar Council of Assam and Nagaland`
  line `shall pass to the Bar Council of Assam Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura.`
  line
  line `(b) The assets and liabilities of the Bar Council of West Bengal shall be apportioned between that Bar`
  line `Council and the Bar Council of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura in such manner and`
  line `proportion as may be agreed upon by the Bar Councils and in default of agreement with reference to any`
  line `matter, the matter shall be referred to the Chairman of the Bar Council of India and his decision thereon`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Expressions used in this section but not defined in this Act shall have the meanings`
  line `assigned to them respectively in the Advocates Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39621)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 46
  title `Practice and procedure in the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39621&sectionno=35&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the`
  line `law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High`
  line `Court of Assam and Nagaland shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common`
  line `High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39622)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 47
  title `Custody of seal of the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39622&sectionno=36&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Assam and Nagaland shall, with`
  line `the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the custody of the seal of the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39623)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 48
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39623&sectionno=37&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Assam`
  line `and Nagaland shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other`
  line `processes used, issued or awarded by the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39624)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 49
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39624&sectionno=38&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Assam and Nagaland`
  line `and with respect to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary`
  line `modifications, apply in relation to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (39625)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 50
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39625&sectionno=39&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Assam and Nagaland and the Judges`
  line `and division courts thereof shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the common High`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (39682)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 51
  title `Transfer of proceedings from the High Court of Assam and Nagaland and the Courts of the Judicial Commissioners to the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39682&sectionno=40&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) All proceedings pending in the High Court of`
  line `Assam and Nagaland and in the Courts of the Judicial Commissioners for Manipur and Tripura`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall, from such day, stand transferred to the common High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding transferred under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of by the common High`
  line `Court as if such proceeding was entertained by that High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made before the appointed day by the High Court of Assam and Nagaland or by the`
  line `Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Manipur or by the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Tripura`
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect not only as an order of that High Court or, as the case may be, of that`
  line `Court but also as an order of the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (39627)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 52
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39627&sectionno=41&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of section 40,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs; and`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof; and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (39628)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 53
  title `Right to appear or act in proceedings transferred to the common High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39628&sectionno=42&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Assam`
  line `and Nagaland or in the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Manipur or in the Court of the Judicial`
  line `Commissioner for Tripura and was authorised to appear or to act in any proceedings transferred from the`
  line `said High Court or Courts of the Judicial Commissioners to the common High Court under section 40,`
  line `shall have the right to appear or to act, as the case may be, in the common High Court in relation to those`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39629)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 54
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39629&sectionno=43&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the common High Court of any`
  line `provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be made on`
  line `or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority having`
  line `power to make such provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39630)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 55
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending sanction by Legislatures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39630&sectionno=44&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President may, at any`
  line `time before the appointed day, authorise by order such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `State of Manipur or of the State of Tripura as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months`
  line `beginning with the appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the State of Manipur or of the State of Tripura, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Manipur or of Tripura may, after the appointed day, authorise by order`
  line `such further expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Manipur or, as`
  line `the case may be, of the State of Tripura for any period not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
  line
  line `(2) The President or, as the case may be, the Governor of the concerned State shall make separate`
  line `orders under sub-section (1) in respect of periods falling in different financial years.`
  line
  line `(3) The Governor of Assam, exercising the functions as Governor in relation to the autonomous State`
  line `of Meghalaya by virtue of the Assam Reorganisation (Meghalaya) Act, 1969 (55 of 1969), may at any`
  line `time, before the appointed day, authorise by order such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the`
  line `State of Meghalaya as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the`
  line `appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of Meghalaya:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Meghalaya may, after the appointed day, authorise such further`
  line `expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Meghalaya for any period`
  line `not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
  line
  line `(4) The Governors referred to in sub-section (3) shall make separate orders under that sub-section in`
  line `respect of periods falling in different financial years.`
  line
  line `(5) The President may, at any time, before or after the appointed day authorise by order such`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of India as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the appointed day for the administration of the affairs of the Union territory of`
  line `Mizoram pending the sanction of such expenditure by Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) The President shall make separate orders under sub-section (5) in respect of periods falling in`
  line `different financial years.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39631)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 56
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure to the Union territory of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39631&sectionno=45&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `Act passed by Parliament for the appropriation of any money out of the Consolidated Fund of India to`
  line `meet the expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year 1971-72 in, or for the purposes of, the`
  line `tribal areas of Assam specified in Part B of the Table appended to paragraph 20 of the Sixth Schedule to`
  line `the Constitution shall, on and from the appointed day, have effect also in relation to the Union territory of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh and it shall be lawful for the President to spend any amount in, or for the purposes of,`
  line `that Union territory out of the amounts authorised by such Act to be expended in, or for the purposes of,`
  line `the said tribal areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39632)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 57
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of the Union territories of Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39632&sectionno=46&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `reports of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in section 49 of the Government of`
  line `Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963) relating to the accounts of the Union territory of Manipur or of`
  line `the Union territory of Tripura in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the`
  line `Governor of Manipur or of Tripura, as the case may be, who shall cause them to be laid before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the State of Manipur or of the State of Tripura, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor of Manipur or of Tripura, as the case may be, may, by order,—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of the Union territory of`
  line `Manipur or of Tripura on any service in respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the`
  line `financial year 1971-72 or in respect of any earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for`
  line `that service and for that year as disclosed in the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly`
  line `authorised, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39633)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 58
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of the autonomous State of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39633&sectionno=47&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports of`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India relating to the accounts of the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya in respect of any period prior to the appointed day shall be submitted to the Governor of`
  line `Meghalaya who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor of Meghalya may, by order,—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya on any service in respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial year`
  line `1971-72 or in respect of any earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service and`
  line `for that year as disclosed in the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39634)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 59
  title `Allowances and privileges of the Governors of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39634&sectionno=48&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and privileges of the Governors of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya and Tripura`
  line `shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under clause (3) of article 158, be such as`
  line `the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (39635)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 60
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39635&sectionno=49&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The President shall, by order, determine the grants-in-aid of the`
  line `revenues of the States of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya and Tripura and the share of each such State in the`
  line `Union duties of excise, estate duty and taxes on income and for that purpose amend thereby the relevant`
  line `provisions of the Union Duties of Excise (Distribution) Act, 1962 (3 of 1962), the Additional Duties of`
  line `Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), the Estate Duty (Distribution) Act, 1962`
  line `(9 of 1962) and the Constitution (Distribution of Revenues) Order, 1969 in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (39636)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 61
  title `Property, assets, rights, liabilities, obligations, etc., of the States of Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39636&sectionno=50&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) All such property and assets within the Union territory of Manipur or of Tripura as are held`
  line `immediately before the appointed day by the Union for purposes of governance of that Union territory`
  line `shall, on and from that day, pass to the State of Manipur or of Tripura, as the case may be, unless the`
  line `purposes for which such property and assets are so held are Union purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cash balance in the treasuries in the Union territory of Manipur or of Tripura before`
  line `the appointed day shall, as from that day, vest in the State of Manipur or of Tripura, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligations (other than those relatable to, or in connection with, a Union`
  line `purpose), whether arising out of any contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before the appointed`
  line day,—
  line
  line `(a) the rights liabilities and obligations of the Central Government arising out of, or in connection`
  line `with, the governance of the Union territory of Manipur or of Tripura; or`
  line
  line `(b) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Administrator of the Union territory of Manipur or`
  line `of Tripura in his capacity as such or of the Government of the Union territory of Manipur or of`
  line Tripura,
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Government of the`
  line `State of Manipur or of Tripura, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The right to recover arrears of—`
  line
  line `(a) any tax or duty being a tax or duty enumerated in the state List in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution, or`
  line
  line `(b) any duty referred to in article 268, or`
  line
  line `(c) any tax under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956),`
  line
  line `which having fallen due in the Union territory of Manipur or of Tripura immediately before the appointed`
  line `day shall, on and from that day, pass to the State of Manipur or of Tripura, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to or in relation to,—`
  line
  line `(a) any institution, undertaking or project the expenditure in relation to which is, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, met from and out of the Consolidated Fund of India;`
  line
  line `(b) any property which has been placed by the Union at the disposal of the administration of the`
  line `Union territory of Manipur or of Tripura subject to the condition that the ownership thereof will`
  line `continue to vest in the Union.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) “liability” includes liability in respect of any civil deposit, local fund deposit, charitable or`
  line `other endowment, provident fund account, pension or actionable wrong;`
  line
  line `(b) “Union purposes” mean the purposes of Government relatable to any of the matters`
  line `mentioned in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (39637)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 62
  title `Assets and liabilities of the State of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39637&sectionno=51&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) All rights, liabilities and obligations`
  line `whether arising out of any contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `rights, liabilities and obligations of the autonomous State of Meghalya, including the rights, liabilities and`
  line `obligations apportioned or to be apportioned to the share of the autonomous State of Meghalaya by virtue`
  line `of section 58 of the Assam Reorganisation (Meghalaya) Act, 1969 (55 of 1969), shall, on and from the`
  line `appointed day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the State of Meghalya.`
  line
  line `(2) All property and assets held by the autonomous State of Meghalya immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, including the property and assets apportioned or to be apportioned to the share of the autonomous State of Mehgalya by virtue of section 58 of the Assam Reorganisation (Meghalaya) Act,`
  line `1969 (55 of 1969) shall, on and from that day, pass to the State of Meghalya.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section and section 52, all rights,`
  line `liabilities and obligations whether arising out of any contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, the rights, liabilities and obligations of the existing State of Assam and all property and`
  line `assets held by the existing State of Assam immediately before the appointed day shall be apportioned`
  line `between the State of Assam and the State of Meghalaya in accordance with the provisions contained in the`
  line `Sixth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (39638)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 63
  title `Assets and liabilities (including public debt) relating to the Mizo District.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39638&sectionno=52&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) All property`
  line `and assets within the Mizo District which are, immediately before the appointed day, vested in the existing`
  line `State of Assam shall, as from that day, vest in the Union.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the Central Government otherwise directs, any stores, articles and other goods belonging to`
  line `the existing State of Assam and situated outside the Mizo District immediately before the appointed day`
  line `shall, as from that day, pass to the Union if such stores, articles or other goods are held for, or are relatable`
  line `to, the administration of that District.`
  line
  line `(3) All rights, liabilities and obligations of the existing State of Assam in relation to the Mizo District`
  line `shall, as from the appointed day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Union.`
  line
  line `(4) The liability of the existing State of Assam to the Union in respect of the loans taken by that State`
  line `from the Central Government shall be reduced by an amount which bears such proportion to the total`
  line `public debt of that State immediately before the appointed day as the total expenditure on all capital works`
  line `and other capital outlays incurred or deemed to have been incurred up to that day by the existing State of`
  line `Assam in the Mizo District bears to the total expenditure on all capital works and other capital outlays`
  line `incurred or deemed to have been incurred by the existing State of Assam up to the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of this sub-section the total public debt of the existing State of Assam`
  line `shall exclude the public debt apportioned or apportionable to the autonomous State of Meghalaya under`
  line `section 58 of the Assam Reorganisation (Meghalaya) Act, 1969 (55 of 1969), and the total expenditure on`
  line `all capital works and other capital outlays incurred or deemed to have been incurred by the existing State`
  line `of Assam shall exclude such outlays incurred or deemed to have been incurred for the purposes of the`
  line `autonomous State under the said section.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall apply to any amount which may be payable by the Union to the`
  line `existing State of Assam in respect of the expenditure incurred by that State in connection with internal`
  line `disturbances in the Mizo District.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (39639)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 64
  title `Provisions as to certain Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1975, s. 2, for "three years" (w.e.f. 20-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39639&sectionno=53&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following bodies corporate constituted for the`
  line `existing State of Assam, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the State Electricity Board constituted under the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948);`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the State Warehousing Corporation established under the Warehousing Corporations Act, 1962`
  line `(58 of 1962),`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which they were`
  line `functioning immediately before that day, subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as`
  line `may, from time to time, be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the Board or`
  line `the Corporation may include a direction that the Act under which the Board or the Corporation was`
  line `constituted shall, in its application to that Board or Corporation, have effect subject to such exceptions and`
  line `modifications as the Central Government thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1) shall cease to function as from, and`
  line `shall be deemed to be dissolved on, the expiry of a period of ^1`
  line `[thirty-eight months] from the appointed day`
  line `or such earlier date as the Central Government may, by order, appoint; and upon such dissolution, its`
  line `assets, rights and liabilities shall be apportioned between the successor States in such manner as may be`
  line `agreed upon among them within one year of the dissolution of the Board or the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or if no agreement is reached, in such manner as the Central Government may, by order,`
  line determine.
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of any of the successor States from constituting at any time on or after the appointed day, a`
  line `State Electricity Board or a State Warehousing Corporation for that State under the provisions of the Act`
  line `relating to such Board or Corporation; and if such a Board or a Corporation is so constituted in any of the`
  line `successor States before the dissolution of the Board or the Corporation referred to in sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) provision may be made by order of the Central Government enabling the new Board or the`
  line `new Corporation to take over from the existing Board or Corporation all or any of its undertakings,`
  line `assets, rights and liabilities in that State, and`
  line
  line `(b) upon the dissolution of the existing Board or Corporation,—`
  line
  line `(i) any assets, rights and liabilities which would otherwise have passed to that State by or`
  line `under the provisions of sub-section (3) shall pass to the new Board or the new Corporation instead`
  line `of to that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) any employees who would otherwise have been transferred to or re-employed by that State`
  line `under sub-section (3), read with clause (i) of sub-section (5), shall be transferred to or`
  line `re-employed by the new Board or the new Corporation instead of to or by that State.`
  line
  line `(5) An agreement entered into between the successor States under sub-section (3) and an order made`
  line `by the Central Government under that sub-section or under clause (a) of sub-section (4) may provide for`
  line `the transfer or re-employment of any employees of the Board or the Corporation referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(i) to or by the successor States, in the case of an agreement under sub-section (3) or an order`
  line `made under that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(ii) to or by the new Board or the new Corporation constituted under sub-section (4), in the case of`
  line `an order made under clause (a) of that sub-section,`
  line
  line `and, subject to the provisions of section 58, also for the terms and conditions of service applicable to such`
  line `employees after such transfer or re-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (39683)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 65
  title `Continuance of arrangements in regard to generation and supply of electric power and supply of water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39683&sectionno=54&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to the Central Government that the arrangement in regard to the generation`
  line `or supply of electric power or the supply of water for any area or in regard to the execution of any project`
  line `for such generation or supply has been or is likely to be modified to the disadvantage of that area by`
  line `reason of the fact that it is, by virtue of the provisions of Part II, outside the State in which the power`
  line `stations and other installations for the generation and supply of such power, or the catchment area,`
  line `reservoirs and other works for the supply of water, as the case may be, are located, the Central`
  line `Government may give such directions as it deems fit, to the State Government or other authority`
  line `concerned for the maintenance, so far as practicable, of the previous arrangement.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (39641)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 66
  title `Provisions as to Assam State Financial Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39641&sectionno=55&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Assam State Financial`
  line `Corporation established under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951) shall, on and from`
  line `the appointed day, continue to function in those areas in respect of which it was functioning immediately`
  line `before that day, subject to the provisions of this section and to such directions as may, from time to time,`
  line `be issued by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of the`
  line `Corporation may include a direction that the said Act, in its application to the Corporation, shall have`
  line `effect subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Board of Directors of`
  line `the Corporation may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and shall, if so required by`
  line `the Central Government, convene at any time after the appointed day a meeting for the consideration of a`
  line `scheme for the reconstitution or reorganisation or dissolution, as the case may be, of the Corporation,`
  line `including proposals regarding the formation of new Corporations, and the transfer thereto of the assets,`
  line `rights and liabilities of the existing Corporation, and if such a scheme is approved at a general meeting by`
  line `a resolution passed by a majority of the shareholders present and voting, the scheme shall be submitted to`
  line `the Central Government for its sanction.`
  line
  line `(4) If the scheme is sanctioned by the Central Government either without modifications or with`
  line `modifications which are approved at a general meeting, the Central Government shall certify the scheme,`
  line `and upon such certification the scheme shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, be binding on the Corporations affected by the scheme as well as the`
  line `shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) If the scheme is not so approved or sanctioned, the Central Government may refer the scheme to`
  line `such Judge of the common High Court as may be nominated in this behalf by the Chief Justice thereof,`
  line `and the decision of the Judge in regard to the scheme shall be final and shall be binding on the`
  line `Corporations affected by the scheme as well as the shareholders and creditors thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in the preceding provisions of this section shall be construed as preventing the`
  line `Government of the State of Meghalaya from constituting, at any time after the appointed day and with the`
  line `approval of the Central Government, a State Financial Corporation for that State under the State Financial`
  line `Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (39642)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 67
  title `General provisions as to statutory corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39642&sectionno=56&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided by`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Part, where any body corporate constituted under a Central Act, State Act`
  line `or Provincial Act for the existing State of Assam or any part thereof has, by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `Part II, become an inter-State body corporate, then, the body corporate shall, on and from the appointed`
  line `day continue to function and operate in those areas in respect of which it was functioning and operating`
  line `immediately before that day, subject to such directions as may from time to time be issued by the Central`
  line `Government, until other provision is made by law in respect of the said body corporate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any directions issued by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in respect of any such`
  line `body corporate may include a direction that any law by which the said body corporate is governed shall, in`
  line `its application to that body corporate, have effect, subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be`
  line `specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (39643)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 68
  title `Temporary provisions as to continuance of certain existing road transport permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39643&sectionno=57&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 63 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939`
  line `(4 of 1939), a permit granted by the State or a Regional Transport Authority in the existing State of Assam`
  line `shall, if such permit was, immediately before the appointed day, valid and effective in any area therein, be`
  line `deemed to continue to be valid and effective in that area after that day subject to the provisions of that Act`
  line `as for the time being in force in that area and it shall not be necessary for any such permit to be`
  line `countersigned by any State or Regional Transport Authority for the purpose of validating it for use in such`
  line `area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned, add to, amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the authority by`
  line `which the permit was granted.`
  line
  line `(2) No tolls, entrance fees or other charges of a like nature shall be levied after the appointed day in`
  line `respect of any transport vehicle for its operations in any of the successor States under any such permit, if`
  line `such vehicle was immediately before that day exempt from the payment of any such tolls, entrance fees or`
  line `other charges for its operations within the existing State of Assam:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government or`
  line `Governments concerned, authorise the levy of any such tolls, entrance fees or other charges, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (39644)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 69
  title `Special provision relating to retrenchment compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39644&sectionno=58&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Where, on account`
  line `of the reorganisation of the existing State of Assam under this Act, any body corporate constituted under a`
  line `Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act, any co-operative society registered under any law relating to`
  line `co-operative societies or any commercial or industrial undertaking of that State is reconstituted or`
  line `reorganised in any manner whatsoever or is amalgamated with any other body corporate, co-operative`
  line `society or undertaking, or is dissolved, and in consequence of such reconstitution, reorganisation,`
  line `amalgamation or dissolution, any workman employed by such body corporate or any such co-operative`
  line `society or undertaking, is transferred to, or re-employed by, any other body corporate, or in any other`
  line `co-operative society or undertaking, then, notwithstanding anything contained in section 25F, 25FF or`
  line `25FFF of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), such transfer or re-employment shall not entitle`
  line `him to any compensation under that section:`
  line
  line `Provided that`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service applicable to the workman after such transfer or`
  line `re-employment are not less favourable to the workman than those applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the transfer or re-employment; and`
  line
  line `(b) the employer in relation to the body corporate, the co-operative society or the undertaking`
  line `where the workman transferred or re-employed is, by agreement or otherwise, legally liable to pay to`
  line `the workman, in the event of his retrenchment, compensation under section 25F, 25FF or 25FFF of the`
  line `Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), on the basis that his service has been continuous and has`
  line `not been interrupted by the transfer or re-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (39645)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 70
  title `Special provisions as to income-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39645&sectionno=59&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where the assets, rights and liabilities of anybody`
  line `corporate carrying on business are, under the provisions of this Part, transferred to any other bodies`
  line `corporate which after the transfer carry on the same business, the losses or profits or gains sustained by the`
  line `body corporate first mentioned which, but for such transfer, would have been allowed to be carried`
  line `forward and set-off in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961), shall be apportioned amongst the transferee bodies corporate in accordance with the rules to`
  line `be made by the Central Government in this behalf and, upon such appointnment, the share of loss allotted`
  line `to each transferee body corporate shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of Chapter VI of`
  line `the said Act as if the transferee body corporate had itself sustained such loss in a business carried on by it`
  line `in the years in which these losses were sustained.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (39646)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 71
  title `Continuance of facilities in certain State institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39646&sectionno=60&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government of the State of`
  line `Assam or Meghalaya or, as the case may be, the Central Government in relation to the Union territory of`
  line `Mizoram shall, in respect of the institutions specified in the Seventh Schedule located in that State or`
  line `Union territory, continue to provide facilities to any other Government aforesaid and the people of the`
  line `States and Union territory aforesaid which shall not, in any respect, be less favourable to such Government`
  line `and people than what were being provided to them before the appointed day, for such period and upon`
  line `such terms and conditions (including those relating to any contributions to be made for the provision of`
  line `such facilities) as may be agreed upon between the said Governments before the expiry of a period of one`
  line `year from the appointed day or, if no agreement is reached before such expiry, as may be fixed by order of`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may at any time before the expiry of a period of one year from the`
  line `appointed day, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in the Seventh Schedule any other institution`
  line `existing on the appointed day in the said States and Union territory and on the issue of such notification,`
  line `the said Schedule shall be deemed to be amended by the inclusion of the said institution therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (39647)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 72
  title `Provisions relating to All-India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39647&sectionno=61&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1)In this section, the expression "joint cadre",--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Police`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954; and`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to the Indian Forest Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Forest`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, there shall be constituted for the States of Assam and Meghalaya a`
  line `joint cadre of the Indian Administrative Service, a joint cadre of the Indian Police Service and a joint cadre`
  line `of the Indian Forest Service.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) On and from the appointed day, there shall be constituted for the States of Manipur and Tripura`
  line `and joint cadre of the Indian Administrative Service, a joint cadre of the Indian Police Service and a joint`
  line `cadre of the Indian Forest Services.]`
  line
  line `(4) The initial strength and composition of each of the joint cadres referred to in sub-sections (2) and`
  line `(3) shall be such as the Central Government may, by order, determine before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(5) The members of each of the said Services borne on the Assam cadre thereof immediately before`
  line `the appointed day shall be allocated to the joint cadre of the same Service constituted under sub-section (2)`
  line `and to the Union territories cadre of that Service in such manner and with effect from such date or dates as`
  line `the Central Government may, by order, specify.`
  line
  line `(6) Such members of each of the said Services borne on the Union territories cadre thereof`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, as the Central Government may, by order, specify, shall be`
  line `allocated to the joint cadre of the same Service constituted under sub-section (3) with effect from such`
  line `date or dates as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(7) Every person who, being a member of a State Civil Service of the existing State of Assam, is borne`
  line `on a Select List for promotion to the Assam cadre of an All-India Service immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall, unless he is deemed to have been allocated to the Union under section 64, be deemed`
  line `to have been included in the same order as in that List, in the Select List for promotion to the joint cadre of`
  line `the same Service constituted under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(8) Every person who, being a person deemed to have been allocated under section 62 for service in`
  line `connection with the affairs of the State of Manipur or the State of Tripura, is borne on a Select List for`
  line `promotion to the Union territories cadre of an All-India Service immediately before the appointed day, shall be deemed to have been included in the same order as in that List, in the Select List for promotion to`
  line `the joint cadre of the same Service constituted under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(9) Every person who, being a person deemed to have been allocated to the Union under section 64, is`
  line `borne on a Select List for promotion to the Assam cadre of an All-India Service immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, shall be deemed to have been included in the Select List for promotion to the Union`
  line `territories cadre of the same Service and his position in the said Select List shall be determined by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Union Public Service Commission.`
  line
  line `(10) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation after the appointed day of the`
  line `All-India Services Act, 1951 (61 of 1951), or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (3) shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 39 of 2012, s. 2 to read as under:`
  line
  line `"(3) On and from the date of commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) Amendment Act, 2012, there`
  line `shall be constituted each for the State of Manipur and for the State of Tripura a separate cadre of the Indian Administrative`
  line `Service, a separate cadre of the Indian Police Service and a separate cadre of the Indian Forest Service.`
  line
  line `(3A) The initial strength and composition of the State cadres referred to in sub-section (1) shall be such as the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, determine before the date of commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 2012.`
  line
  line `(3B) The members of each of the said services borne on the joint cadre for the States of Manipur and Tripura in each`
  line `category of the All-India Services immediately before the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation)`
  line `Amendment Act, 2012 shall be allocated to the State cadres of the same service constituted under sub-section (1) in such manner`
  line `and with effect from such date or dates as the Central Government may, by order, specify.`
  line
  line `(3C) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation, on or after the commencement of the North-Eastern`
  line `Areas (Reorganisation) Amendment Act, 2012, of the All-India Services Act, 1951 (61 of 1951), or the rules and regulations`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (39648)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 73
  title `Provision relating to Services in Manipur and Tripura.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39648&sectionno=62&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Every person who immediately before`
  line `the appointed day is serving in connection with the affairs of the Union under the administrative control of`
  line `the Administrator of the Union territory of Manipur, or the Administrator of the Union territory of Tripura`
  line `(including a person who has been placed on deputation by the Administrator concerned with any other`
  line `authority), shall, unless otherwise directed by an order of the Central Government, be deemed to have`
  line `been allocated for service as from that day in connection with the affairs of the State of Manipur or, as the`
  line `case may be, of the State of Tripura:`
  line
  line `Provided that no direction shall be issued under this section after the expiry of a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (39649)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 74
  title `Special provisions relating to members of Central Health Service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39649&sectionno=63&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the`
  line `provisions of section 62, every member of the Central Health Service who immediately before the`
  line `appointed day is holding any post in the Union territory of Manipur or the Union territory of Tripura,`
  line `being a post included in the authorised strength of that Service, shall, unless otherwise directed by the`
  line `Central Government, be deemed to be on deputation on and from the appointed day, to the Government of`
  line `the State of Manipur or, as the case may be, of the State of Tripura on the same terms and conditions of`
  line `service as are applicable to him under the Central Health Service Rules, 1963, but without any deputation`
  line `allowance:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of such deputation shall in no case extend beyond a period of three years from`
  line `the appointed day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "Central Health Service" means the Central Health Service constituted`
  line `under the Central Health Service Rules, 1963.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (39650)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 75
  title `Provisions relating to Services in the existing State of Assam.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39650&sectionno=64&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such persons serving in`
  line `connection with the affairs of the existing State of Assam (including persons borne on any cadre of that`
  line `State and serving under the Government of the autonomous State of Meghalaya or on deputation to any`
  line `other Government or authority) as may be determined at any time before or after the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) by agreement between the Government of the existing State of Assam and the Government of`
  line `the autonomous State of Meghalaya or between the Government of the State of Assam and the`
  line `Government of the State of Meghalaya, as the case may be, or`
  line
  line `(b) in default of any such agreement, by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `may, notwithstanding anything in their terms of appointment or their conditions of service,—`
  line
  line `(i) in a case referred to in clause (a), by one or more orders made by the Government of the`
  line `existing State of Assam or the Government of the State of Assam, as the case may be, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case referred to in clause (b), by one or more orders made by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `be required to serve in connection with the affairs of the State of Meghalaya and every such person shall`
  line `accordingly be deemed to have been allocated to that State with effect from such date as may be specified`
  line `in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Such persons serving in connection with the affairs of the existing State of Assam (including`
  line `persons borne on any cadre of the existing State of Assam and serving under the Government of the autonomous State of Meghalaya or on deputation to any other Government or authority), as the Central`
  line `Government may, at any time before or after the appointed day, determine after consultation with the`
  line `Government of the existing State of Assam or the Government of the State of Assam, as the case may be,`
  line `may, notwithstanding anything in the terms of their appointment or their conditions of service, by one or`
  line `more orders made by the Central Government, be required to serve in connection with the administration`
  line `of the Union territory of Mizoram, and every such person shall, accordingly, be deemed to have been`
  line `allocated to the Union with effect from such date as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that every person borne on any cadre of the existing State of Assam and serving in the Mizo`
  line `District immediately before the appointed day shall, unless otherwise directed by the Administrator of the`
  line `Union territory of Mizoram, continue to serve on and from the appointed day, in connection with the`
  line `administration of that Union territory until any order is made under this sub-section in respect of such`
  line `person or the expiry of a period of three years from the appointed day, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (39651)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 76
  title `Provisions relating to Services in the autonomous State of Meghalaya.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39651&sectionno=65&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Every person who`
  line `immediately before the appointed day is serving in connection with the affairs of the autonomous State of`
  line `Meghalaya (including a person on deputation from the Government of that autonomous State to any other`
  line `Government or authority), not being a person to whom section 64 applies, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `allocated to serve as from that day in connection with the affairs of the State of Meghalaya.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (39652)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 77
  title `Other provisions relating to Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39652&sectionno=66&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this section or sections 62 to 65 (both`
  line `inclusive) shall be deemed to affect on or after the appointed day the operation of the provisions of`
  line `Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution in relation to determination of conditions of service of persons`
  line `serving in connection with the affairs of the State of Manipur, Meghalaya or Tripura or the Union territory`
  line `of Mizoram:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of`
  line `any person deemed to have been allocated to the State of Manipur or the State of Tripura under section 62`
  line `or to the State of Meghalaya under sub-section (1) of section 64 or section 65 or to the Union under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 64 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person—`
  line
  line `(a) if he is deemed to have been allocated to any State under section 62 or section 64 or`
  line `section 65, shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of that State,`
  line
  line `(b) if he is deemed to have been allocated to the Union in connection with the administration of`
  line `the Union territory of Mizoram, shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the Union,`
  line
  line `for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sections 62, 64 and 65 shall not apply in relation to members of any All-India`
  line Service.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (39653)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 78
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39653&sectionno=67&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the`
  line `administration of the Union territory of Manipur or Union territory of Tripura, shall continue to hold the`
  line `same post or office in the State of Manipur, or, as the case may be, in the State of Tripura and shall be`
  line `deemed, on and from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or`
  line `other appropriate authority in the State concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person who immediately before the appointed day is holding or discharging the duties of`
  line `any post or office in connection with the affairs of the existing State of Assam and, as from the appointed`
  line `day, such duties become duties in connection with the affairs of the State of Meghalaya or administration`
  line `of the Union territory of Mizoram, then, he shall continue to hold the same post or office in that State or`
  line `Union territory and shall be deemed, on and from that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or`
  line `office by the Government or Administrator of, or other appropriate authority in, that State or Union`
  line `territory, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person who immediately before the appointed day is holding or discharging the duties of`
  line `any post or office in connection with the affairs of the autonomous State of Meghalaya and, as from the`
  line `appointed day, such duties become duties in connection with the affairs of the State of Meghalaya, then, he`
  line `shall continue to hold the same post or office in the State of Meghalaya and shall be deemed, on and from`
  line `that day, to have been duly appointed to the post or office by the Government of, or other appropriate`
  line `authority in, the State of Meghalaya.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) shall be deemed to prevent a`
  line `competent authority, on and from the appointed day, from passing in relation to any person referred to in`
  line `that sub-section any order affecting his continuance in such post or office.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (39654)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 79
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39654&sectionno=68&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order, establish one or more Advisory`
  line `Committees for the purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the discharge of any of its functions under this Part; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `Part and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (39655)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 80
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39655&sectionno=69&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the State Governments of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya and Tripura and to the Administrator`
  line `of the Union territory of Mizoram as may appear to it to be necessary for the purpose of giving effect to`
  line `the foregoing provisions of this Part and the State Governments and the Administrator shall comply with`
  line `such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (39656)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 81
  title `Provisions as to State Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39656&sectionno=70&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Service Commission for the`
  line `existing State of Assam shall, on and from the appointed day, be deemed to be the Public Service`
  line `Commission for the State of Assam.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person holding office immediately before the appointed day as Chairman or other member`
  line `of the Public Service Commission for the existing State of Assam shall, as from the appointed day, be the`
  line `Chairman or, as the case may be, the other member of the Public Service Commission for the State of`
  line Assam.
  line
  line `(3) Every person who becomes Chairman or other member of the Public Service Commission for the`
  line `State of Assam on the appointed day under sub-section (2) shall—`
  line
  line `(a) be entitled to receive from the Government of the State of Assam conditions of service not less`
  line `favourable than those to which he was entitled under the provisions applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the appointed day; and`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the proviso to clause (2) of article 316, hold office or continue to hold office until`
  line `the expiration of his term of office as determined under the provisions applicable to him immediately`
  line `before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (39684)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 82
  title `Amendment of articles 210, 239A, 244, 244A, 275, 332, 371B and Fifth and Sixth Schedules to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39684&sectionno=71&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day—`
  line
  line `(a) in article 210, in the proviso to clause (2), for the words “Legislature of the State of Himachal Pradesh”, the words “Legislatures of the States of Himachal Pradesh, Manipur, Meghalaya and Tripura” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in article 239A, in clause (1), the words “Manipur, Tripura,” shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(c) in article 244,—`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (1), for the words “the State of Assam”, the words “the States of Assam and Meghalaya” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (2), for the words “the State of Assam”, the words “the States of Assam and Meghalaya and the Union territory of Mizoram” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(d) in article 244A, in clause (1), for the word and letter “Part A”, the word and figure “Part I” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(e) in article 275, in clause (a) of the second proviso to clause (1), for the word and letter “Part A”, the word and figure “Part I” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(f) in article 332,—`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (5), the words “except in the case of the constituency comprising the cantonment and municipality of shillong” shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (6), the words “except from the constituency comprising the cantonment and municipality of Shillong” shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(g)in article 371B, for the word and letter “Part A”, the word and figure “Part I” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(h)in the Fifth Schedule to the Constitution, in paragraph 1, for the words “State of Assam”, the words “States of Assam and Meghalaya” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(i) the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution shall stand amended as directed in the Eighth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (39658)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 83
  title `Amendment of Act 2 of 1934.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39658&sectionno=72&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in section 21A of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934, in sub-section (1), the brackets and words in the Fifth Schedule to the Constitution, in paragraph 1, for the words “(including the autonomous State of Meghalaya)” shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (39659)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 84
  title `Amendment of Act 64 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39659&sectionno=73&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in section 47A of the Road`
  line `Transport Corporations Act, 1950, in the Explanation to sub-section (1), after clause (ii), the following`
  line `clause shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“(iii) in relation to the Assam State Road Transport Corporation, shall mean the Government of the State of Assam or of Meghalaya as formed under the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) Act, 1971.”.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (39660)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 85
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39660&sectionno=74&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956,—`
  line
  line `(a) for clause (c) of section 15, the following clause shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“(c) the Eastern Zone, comprising the States of Bihar, West Bengal and Orissa;”;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (1) of section 16, clause (d) shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (39661)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 86
  title `Amendment of Act 20 of 1963.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39661&sectionno=75&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the Government of Union`
  line `Territories Act, 1963,—`
  line
  line `(a) in clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 2, the words “Manipur, Tripura,” shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) in section 44, sub-section (2) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(c) section 52 shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (39662)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 87
  title `Amendment of Act 56 of 1955 and the Tripura (Courts) Order, 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39662&sectionno=76&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `On and from the`
  line `appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Manipur (Courts) Act, 1955 shall stand amended as directed in the Ninth Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) the Tripura (Courts) Order, 1950 shall stand amended as directed in the Tenth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (39663)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 88
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39663&sectionno=77&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of Part II shall not be deemed to have effected any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and the territorial references in any such law to the existing State of Assam or the autonomous`
  line `State of Meghalaya or the Union territory of Manipur or the Union territory of Tripura or the North-East Frontier Agency shall, until otherwise provided by a competent Legislature or other competent authority,`
  line `be construed as meaning the territories within that State or autonomous State or Union territory or Agency`
  line `immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (39664)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 89
  title `Continuance of existing District Councils and Regional Council and members thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39664&sectionno=78&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line For
  line `the removal of doubt, it is hereby declared that all District Councils and the Regional Council constituted`
  line `under the provisions of the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution and functioning immediately before the`
  line `appointed day in the respective autonomous districts and in the autonomous region shall, as from that day,`
  line `be deemed to have been constituted under the said Schedule as amended by clause (i) of section 71, read`
  line `with the Eighth Schedule and accordingly,—`
  line
  line `(a) every such District Council and the Regional Council shall, unless sooner dissolved, continue`
  line `to function in the respective autonomous districts and in the autonomous region, notwithstanding that`
  line `any such district or region ceases to be comprised in the territories of the State of Assam, by virtue of`
  line `the provisions of Part II; and`
  line
  line `(b) every member of such District Council or Regional Council shall continue to be a member`
  line `thereof for the unexpired term of his office as such.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (39665)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 90
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39665&sectionno=79&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application of any law in relation to any`
  line `of the States of Union territories formed or established by the provisions of Part II, the appropriate`
  line `Government may, before the expiration of two years from the appointed day, by order, make such`
  line `adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as may be necessary or`
  line `expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations and modifications so`
  line `made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "the appropriate Government" means—`
  line
  line `(a) as respects any law relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule`
  line `to the Constitution, the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) as respects any other law,—`
  line
  line `(i) in its application to a State, the State Government, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in its application to a Union territory, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (39666)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39666&sectionno=80&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has`
  line `been made under section 79 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal`
  line `or authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application`
  line `in relation to the State of Assam, Manipur, Meghalaya or Tripura or to the Union territory of Mizoram or`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance, as may be necessary`
  line `or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference to the High Court of Assam or the High Court of Assam and Nagaland or to the`
  line `Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Manipur or the Court of the Judicial Commissioner for Tripura in`
  line `any law shall, unless the context otherwise requires, be construed, on and from the appointed day, as a`
  line `reference to the common High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (39667)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 92
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39667&sectionno=81&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government,`
  line `as respects the Union territory of Mizoram or Arunachal Pradesh and the State Government as respects`
  line `any new State established or formed by the provisions of Part II may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify the authority, officer or person who, as from the appointed day, shall be competent to`
  line `exercise such functions exercisable under any law in force on that day as may be mentioned in that`
  line `notification and such law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (39668)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 93
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39668&sectionno=82&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where immediately before the appointed day the Union is a party to any`
  line `legal proceedings with respect to any property, right or liability and such property, right or liability`
  line `devolves on the State of Manipur or the State of tripura under this Act, then, the State of Manipur or, as`
  line `the case may be, the State of Tripura shall be deemed to be substituted for the Union as a party to those`
  line `proceedings and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Where immediately before the appointed day the autonomous State of Meghalaya is a party to any`
  line `legal proceedings with respect to any property, right or liability of that State, and such property, right or`
  line `liability devolves on the State of Meghalaya under this Act, then, the State of Meghalaya shall be deemed`
  line `to be substituted for the autonomous State of Meghalaya as a party to those proceedings and the`
  line `proceedings may continue accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Where immediately before the appointed day the existing State of Assam is a party to any legal`
  line `proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities subject to apportionment under this Act, the`
  line `successor State, which succeeds to, or acquires a share in, that property or those rights or liabilities by`
  line `virtue of any provision of this Act, shall be deemed to be substituted for the existing State of Assam as a`
  line `party to those proceedings or added as a party thereto, as the case may be, and the proceedings may`
  line `continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (39669)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 94
  title `Rights of pleaders to practise in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39669&sectionno=83&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the existing State of`
  line `Assam shall, for a period of one year from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those courts,`
  line `notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts has been`
  line `transferred to the State of Meghalaya or to a Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (39670)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 95
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39670&sectionno=84&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within a State or Union territory shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to the`
  line `territories which as from that day are the territories of another State or Union territory, stand transferred to`
  line `the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in that other State or Union territory, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the common High Court and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,,—`
  line
  line `(a) “proceeding” includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) “corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer” in a State or a Union territory means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State or Union territory in which or before`
  line `whom the proceeding would have lain if it had been instituted after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State or Union territory as`
  line `may be determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State or the Central`
  line `Government, as the case may be, or before the appointed day by the Government of the existing`
  line `State of Assam or the Government of the autonomous State of Meghalaya or the Central`
  line `Government, as the case may be, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (39671)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 96
  title `Provisions as to continuance of courts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39671&sectionno=85&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `All courts and tribunals and all authorities`
  line `discharging lawful functions throughout the existing State of Assam or the Union territory of Manipur or`
  line `the Union territory of Tripura or any part of such State or Union territory immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall, unless their continuance is inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or until other`
  line `provision is made by a competent Legislature or other competent authority, continue to exercise their`
  line `respective functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (39672)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 97
  title `Effect of provisions of the Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39672&sectionno=86&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (39673)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39673&sectionno=87&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to him`
  line `to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87_a:
  sectionId (39674)
  sectionNo 87A
  orderNo 99
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2012, s. 8 (w.e.f. 23-3-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39674&sectionno=87A&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_87_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[87A. Power to remove difficulties.—(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, as amended by the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) and Other Related Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2012.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (39675)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 100
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1974, s. 3, for “which may be comprised in one session or in two successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the session immediately following” (w.e.f. 19-1-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607&sectionId=39675&sectionno=88&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00012_197181_1517807319607
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days ^1`
  line `[which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
